Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows significantly elevated creatinine, proteinuria, glycosuria, ketonuria, and bilirubinuria, with low urine specific gravity and abnormal urine appearance, suggesting impaired renal function, likely acute or chronic kidney disease with possible tubular involvement. Blood glucose and HbA1c are normal, making diabetes less likely. No evidence of urinary tract infection. Recommend further nephrological evaluation and assessment for possible underlying causes of renal impairment.
